@node "SecIntro"

   @{b}Introduction@{ub}

Welcome to MagnifiCAD. MagnifiCAD is a computer-aided design program, which allows you to produce drawings in 2D with the help of a variety of tools. 

MagnifiCAD supports different line styles, hatching, colors, and can exchange files with other CAD packages supporting the DXF file format. 

   @{"System Requirements" Link "IntroSyste"}
   @{"Registration" Link "IntroRegis"}
   @{"Drawing elements and their representation" Link "IntroDrawi"}
@endnode

@node "SecScreen" 
   
   @{b}Screen Elements@{ub}

The default MagnifiCAD screen setup consists of two windows: the Tools Palette and a Project Window. In addition to these, other palettes can also be displayed.
   
   @{"Tools Palette" Link "ScreenTools"}
   @{"Project Window" Link "ScreenProje"}
@endnode

@node "SecTypes"

   @{b}Types of drawing tools	@{ub}

The tool palette contains all the tools you need to draw. The tools are divided into modifiers and operators.

@{"The drawing modifier tools" Link "TypesModif"} are the element generation modifiers and the self/copy modifiers.

@{"The drawing operators" Link "TypesOpera"} are the element generation tools, pick/delete tools, geometric transformations and attribute assignments.
@endnode

@node "SecGener"

	@{b}Generating elements@{ub}

The drawing tools are used to create different drawing elements. When you select a tool, instructions will be shown in the text information bar about what the tool does.

Any time during a drawing operation, you can press the right mouse button to cancel the process. The rubberbanding will be deleted from the screen.

The Shift keys can be used to close a polyline or a polycurve.
@endnode

@node "SecPicki"

   @{b}Picking@{ub}

When the user wants to edit an object, that is, apply a transformation or delete it, the object must be picked. 
   
   @{"Prepick and Postpick" Link "PickiPrepi"}
   @{"The Pick Tool" Link "Tool_Pick"}
   @{"Unpicking" Link "PickiUnpic"}
@endnode

@node "SecDelet"

@{b}Delete@{ub}

Delete is used when an element is to be erased from the project.

   @{"The Delete Tool" Link "Tool_Delete"}
@endnode

@node "SecGeome"
	
   @{b}Geometric Transformations@{ub}

The Geometric Transformations operate on an element to change its geometry. The Self/Copy modifiers affect the transformations.

	
   @{"The Self/Copy Modifiers" Link "GeomeModif"}
   @{"The Geometric Transformations" Link "GeomeTrans"}
   @{"Transforming Objects" Link "GeomeObjec"}
@endnode

@node "SecEleme"

   @{b}Element Attributes@{ub}

All the drawing elements have attributes that can be set and changed. These attributes are color, line style, line weight, hatch and the layer they are in.

Some elements are affected by all these attributes, and some are affected by some of them, as shown in the table below.

            Color	Style	Weight	Hatch		Layer
-----------------------------------------------
Point         o    o      o       -       o
Line          o    o      o       -       o
Polyline      o	   o      o 	    o	      o
Polycurve	    o    o      o 		  o       o
Rectangle     o	   o      o       o       o
Polyform      o	   o      o       o       o
Circle	      o	   o      o       -       o
Ellipse	      o	   o      o 			-       o
Arc           o	   o      o 			-       o
Text		      o	   -      - 			-       o
Group         -    -      -       -       o
Symbol	      o	   -      -       -       o
-----------------------------------------------

   @{"Setting the element attributes" Link "ElemeSetti"}
@endnode

@node "SecSymbo"

   @{b}Symbols@{ub}

Symbols are used in a drawing to represent elements that are repetitioned. They can be used to standard symbolic representation like doors, windows, furniture, etc. in drawings.

Symbols are not affected by the hatch attribute, and they may not be rotated.

   @{"Creating Symbols" Link "SymbolCreateSymbol"}
   @{"Placing Symbols" Link "SymbolPlaceSymbol"}
   @{"Exploding Symbols" Link "SymbolExplodeSymbol"}
@endnode

@node "SecSnapM"

   @{b}The Snap Modes@{ub}

The Snap modes determine what happens to the input coordinates, if they are adjusted (snapped), and to where. When an input point is snapped, the actual coordinate recorded is changed to fit the current snap mode.
      
   @{"Grid snap" Link "SnapMGridS"}
   @{"Directional snap" Link "SnapMDirec"}
   
	 @{"Object snaps" Link "SnapMObjec"}
@endnode


@node "IntroSyste"

   @{b}System Requirements@{ub}

MagnifiCAD requires:

   o An Amiga with Workbench 3.0 or above, preferrably with a 68020
     processor or higher.    

   o about 1MB free memory.

MagnifiCAD can run with only about 500K memory free, but will need more memory for large projects.

The size of the projects is limited only by how much free memory you have in your Amiga. 
@endnode

