@node "AppUsing"

   @{b}Appendix A: Using MagnifiCAD with other CAD programs@{ub}

MagnifiCAD can be used in conjunction with other CAD type programs, both on the Amiga and on other platforms. Use one of the supported file formats to transfer a project into another program.


Supported File Formats

The only currently supported file format is the DXF drawing files.

   @{"AutoCAD DXF 2D" Link "AppUsiAutoc"
@endnode

@node "AppUsiAutoc"

   @{b}AutoCAD DXF 2D@{ub}

MagnifiCAD reads and writes AutoCAD DXF files. This is the most standard filetype for CAD drawings, and may be imported into a variety of packages.

DXF files are divided into sections. MagnifiCAD reads the HEADER section, the TABLES section, and the ENTITY section.

The supported tables in the TABLES section are:
   
  LAYER

The supported entities are:

	LINE
	POLYLINE
	CIRCLE
	ARC
	TEXT

@endnode

@node "AppSpeed"

   @{b}Appendix B - Speed and Memory Issues@{ub}

MagnifiCAD is supposed to work decently on an unexpanded A1200, but it will be rather slow. To speed things up a bit, there are several things that can be done.

· Select the normal HIRES screenmode, without interlace, and with few colors (16).
· Close the color and hatch palettes. 

MagnifiCAD runs with just 500K free memory, but allocates memory for each element added to a project. An unexpanded A1200 has 2 megabytes of memory. This should be enough for quite large projects. If you run out of memory, try closing other programs that are running and choose a screenmode with low resolution.

The amount of free memory available can be checked by choosing About in the Project menu.
@endnode

@node "AppKeybo"

   @{b}Appendix C -  Keyboard Shortcuts@{ub}

All keyboard shortcuts consists of pressing the Amiga Key(A) and another key, as shown in the table below.

   Key 
   (A+) Command              Menu

   A    Save as...           (Project Menu)
   B    Move to Back         (Arrange Menu)
   C    Copy                 (Edit Menu)
   E    Entity Info          (Arrange Menu)
   F    Move to Front        (Arrange Menu)
   G    Group                (Arrange Menu)
   H    Help                 (Help Menu)
   I    Zoom In              (View Menu)
   L    Layers               (Arrange Menu)
   N    New                  (Project Menu)
   O    Open                 (Project Menu)
   P    Print                (Project Menu)
   Q    Quit                 (Project Menu)
   R    Redraw               (View Menu)
   S    Save                 (Project Menu)
   U    Ungroup              (Arrange Menu)
   V    Paste                (Edit Menu)
   W    Views                (View Menu)
   X    Cut                  (Edit Menu)
   Z    Zoom Out By Factor   (View Menu)
   
   0-9  ARexx Macro #0-#9
@endnode

